EXIF is data stored in digital picture files about the picture itself. Its also a command line tool to extract and manipulate this information.

### Related Pages
* [[exiftool]]
* [[IPTC]]
* [[XMP]]

I use this command to remove some basic exif tags to further reduce filesize:
<pre>
exiftool -ThumbnailImage= -Software= -FirmwareRevision= -FlashpixVersion= -ColorSpace= -ExposureMode= -FileSource= -SensingMethod= -CustomRendered= -Flash= -Orientation= -ImageUniqueID= -MeteringMode= -ShutterSpeedValue= -WhiteBalance=
</pre>

